12/01/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou announced a diplomatic tour of the western Balkans, to begin Monday (13 January). 
Papandreou will visit Macedonia, Croatia and Yugoslavia. 
Papandreou will then attend Thursday's inaugural ceremony of the EU police in Bosnia and Herzegovina, and make a final stop in Kosovo before returning to Greece. 
Papandreou told reporters on Saturday that the EU rapid reaction force should be ready in May. 
Greece took over the EU's rotating presidency at the start of 2003. 
(Athens News Agency, Macedonian Press Agency, Kathimerini, AFP - 11/01/03)
